post_text:
***HIGH SCHOOL REGISTRATION***

Please be aware that registration will be on Wednesday August 12th from 1-3pm. We ask that parents come with students in the timeframe given for each grade level. This will help prevent congestion/crowding and make the overall process more smooth. Timeframes below..

9th grade: 1:00-1:30pm

10th grade: 1:30-2:00pm

11th grade: 2:00-2:30pm

12th grade: 2:30-3:00pm

Students will have an opportunity to look at supply lists for each class when they register. If students happen to miss registration on the 12th, they will receive a list on the first day of school.

Please limit to one parent/guardian. If a parent has multiple students in different grade levels, they can pick one time and get it all taken care of at that point.

Understand we would like everyone to follow guidelines for Covid-19 during this time. If anyone has questions, please call the high school office. Thank you.

post_text:
Menard ISD has released our official ‚ÄúBack to School Survey‚Äù on the school website at www.menardisd.net. We need it completed by August 5th so we can get the data together for both sets of students. Please make sure you understand that home based learning or in class instruction is your choice as a parent or guardian. Each six weeks you can reevaluate your choice prior to the new six weeks starting.

The virtual home learning will be different than last year‚Äôs packets. The Texas Education Agency has put rules and guidance in place for us to create a plan. Your child will have to check in, watch teaching, participate in lessons, and turn in work daily for each subject. If your child does not engage daily, then they will be counted absent for that day. They will be graded on the work that they are doing, and it will not be pass/fail. High school course credit is determined by daily attendance in each class.

Menard ISD at this time will only allow participation in extracurricular if your child is attending in class instruction.

We are excited to begin summer workouts again starting Monday, July 13th. The girls will continue to meet outside the old gym and workout from 8am - 10am, Monday through Thursday. The boys will now meet outside the weight room and continue to workout 6pm - 8pm, Monday through Thursday. We will also offer open gym (old gym) and weight room from 8am - 3pm, Monday through Thursday.

We will continue to follow COVID guidelines with checking temperatures and symptoms checks to ensure the health of our student/athletes and will now require each student and any parents attending workouts to wear a mask.

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text:
Let's talk grades.
We want our students to be successful and pass if they are doing the work. The school board passed a resolution that said we didn‚Äôt have to have the required number of grades as before. It also changed how we grade. It is truly a pass/ fail semester. The numerical grades in the grade book are kind of like place holders in the grading system, simply put, and at the end of the semester, we can print final report cards. The end of semester grade will be pass/fail. Teachers are inputting numerical grades, but in the end, it will be either pass or fail, as a whole semester. One incomplete packet will not keep a student from passing for the semester, but multiple incomplete packets may.
Remember, if you receive an "F" (fail) at the end of the semester, you will not receive credit for the class and it will have to be taken again in the fall. Turn you packets in!!! Contact us for help, we are here for you!! Together, we can do this.

post_text:
As per the Executive Order issued by the Governor Abbott of Texas, Menard ISD will be closed but providing home based learning through May 1st. We will provide meals during this closure on Mondays and Thursdays from 11:30-12:30 at the elementary & junior high. We will have packet drop off and pick up April 7th, April 14th, April 21st, and April 28th at your child‚Äôs campus from 11:30-12:30. It is imperative that your child is completing these packets. The home based learning documents will be used to determine mastery of grade level and/or course credit. Please contact the teachers by Remind or email if your child needs help. The teachers have also set up other forms of communication to help. The teachers are here to help you during the week.

Thanks to all of you for the continued effort for our school, students, and community. We will all need to work together and with our neighbors.

post_text:
Update from UIL:

To support the health and safety of our students and communities, UIL is suspending all UIL sanctioned contests due to the outbreak of COVID-19 (Coronavirus) in Texas. Effective March 16th, all UIL interscholastic competition is suspended until March 29th. At this time, competitions may resume on March 30th. We are in contact with state authorities and will continue to monitor this situation. Should further adjustments be necessary, we will communicate them to you as soon as they are available.

During this time competitions are suspended, practices and rehearsals may be held at the discretion of the local school district.

Menard ISD will not be attending golf tournaments, softball games, tennis tournaments, UIL academics, or track meets for the next two weeks.

post_text: Congratulations Roy. It‚Äôs a great day to be a Yellowjacket
shared_text:
Menard Yellowjacket Band
January 11 at 10:29 PM ¬∑

Roy Brown attended the Levelland Area auditions today where he placed... 1st chair. Out of all the 1-3a and 9th-12th grade students, Roy was the one to beat! Pretty amazing.

Roy is a great musician but above everything, Roy is a great example of what the world needs more of.

Roy will spend a week in San Antonio preparing for the All-State band concert that will take place on February 15th. He will be auditioning for his placement in the All-State band on February 12th!

Congratulations on a job well done.

Menard Yellowjacket Band
November 7, 2019 at 9:59 AM ¬∑

We couldn‚Äôt be prouder of our band for earning 5th Place at the State Marching Contest! The band worked incredibly hard this season, earned straight first division ratings from all three judges at Region Marching Contest, competed against the best 1A bands in the state at the Alamodome, qualified for finals (multiple judges even ranked us first in prelims!) and had the best performance of the year in finals. This is the highest placement the Menard band has earned in school history! We‚Äôre so grateful to the students, parents, administration, and everyone who made this happen. This has been an amazing journey that we‚Äôll never forget!

Angelo State University Music was celebrating success.
November 6, 2019 at 10:33 AM ¬∑

Congratulations to the Irion County Hornet Marching Band and their director Brian Tillman (an ASU alum) for winning the 2019 1A State Marching Band Competition. Also congratulations to the Eden Bulldog Marching Band and their director Brit Britt McCulloch (another ASU alum) for finishing third and the Menard Yellowjacket Marching Band and their director Lynsey Gold (ANOTHER ASU alum) for finishing 5th. We are very proud of your accomplishments this season and look forward to the many great things to come this year.

post_text:
Biology EOC Review

All Biology students who will be taking the EOC on May 8th are required to attend after school Biology EOC review for a total of 2 hours. Sessions are scheduled for Thursday, April 25 and every day Monday - Thursday, April 29 - May 2.

Attendance for 2 hours = 100 test grade
Attendance for 1 hour = 50 test grade
Attendance for less than 1 hour = 0 test grade

Sessions are from 3:30 to 5:30 each day in the kitchen area at the high school. Mrs. Nixon will stay until 6:00 any of those days if you let her know ahead of time. You will be required to sign in and out and record your times.

Please do not wait until the last day to try to get your entire 2 hours. It will be much more effective if you divide the time over 2 days and usually the first two days are not as crowded!

Workforce Solutions Summer Youth Employment

If you are interested in the summer employment program through Workforce Solutions, you will need to attend a meeting on Tuesday, May 14th. The meeting will be at the community center and will begin at 3:30 and last until 5:30.

To qualify for the summer work program, you need to be 16 years old by June 1 and qualify for the free and reduced lunch program.

Applications need to be completed before this meeting. If you need an application, see Mrs. Laxson.

If you cannot attend this meeting on May 14th, there are two trainings available in San Angelo. One is on April 19th from 9 to 4 and the second one is on May 3rd from 9 to 4. If you would like information on those meetings contact Araceli Hernandez at (325) 653-2321 ext. 1230

felicia.laxson@menardisd.net or 325-396-2513
